## Best Practices

### 1. **Theme-Aware Components**

Always support both light and dark modes:

```javascript
const { theme } = useTheme();
const isDark = theme === "dark";

<div className={`
  p-6 rounded-lg border
  ${isDark 
    ? "bg-[#111111] border-white/5 text-white" 
    : "bg-white border-gray-200 text-gray-900"
  }
`}>
```

### 2. **Consistent Color Palette**

Use the custom color system defined in Tailwind config:

```javascript
// ✅ Good - Uses theme colors
bg-[#81E6D9]           // Brand cyan
text-[#787878]         // Dark mode secondary text
border-white/10        // Dark mode borders

// ❌ Avoid - Random colors
bg-blue-400
text-gray-700
```

### 3. **Component Reusability**

Extract repeated patterns into shared components:

```javascript
// Instead of repeating button styles everywhere
<button className="px-6 py-3 bg-[#81E6D9] rounded-full...">

// Use the Button component
<Button variant="primary" size="md">Click Me</Button>
```

### 4. **Animation Guidelines**

- Use `once: true` for scroll animations to avoid re-triggering
- Set viewport margins (`margin: "-100px"`) to trigger before fully visible
- Stagger children animations by 0.1s intervals
- Keep hover animations under 0.3s
- Use GPU-accelerated properties only

### 5. **Accessibility**

```javascript
// Semantic HTML
<section>, <header>, <nav>, <footer>

// ARIA labels
<button aria-label="Toggle theme">
  <ThemeIcon />
</button>

// Keyboard navigation
<a 
  href="/pricing"
  className="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#81E6D9]"
>
```

### 6. **Custom Scrollbar Styling**

```css
/* Webkit browsers (Chrome, Safari) */
::-webkit-scrollbar {
  width: 10px;
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
  background: #0a0a0a;
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
  background: #333333;
  border-radius: 5px;
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
  background: #444444;
}

/* Firefox */
* {
  scrollbar-width: thin;
  scrollbar-color: #333333 #0a0a0a;
}
```

### 7. **Performance Optimizations**

```javascript
// Lazy load components
const FeaturesGrid = lazy(() => import('./components/landing/FeaturesGrid'));

// Optimize images
<img 
  src="/hero.webp" 
  loading="lazy" 
  alt="Dashboard preview"
/>

// Code splitting by route
<Route path="/pricing" element={<Pricing />} />
```

### 8. **Consistent Spacing Scale**

Use Tailwind's spacing scale consistently:

| Scale | Value | Common Usage |
|-------|-------|--------------|
| `4` | 1rem (16px) | Small gaps |
| `6` | 1.5rem (24px) | Default padding |
