## Key Takeaways for Prompting

When building similar websites, include these elements in your prompts:

### Design System Prompt

```
Use Tailwind CSS with a custom color palette that includes:
- Primary brand color (#81E6D9 cyan) for CTAs and highlights
- Full light/dark theme support with context-specific colors
- Typography: DM Sans for body, DM Mono for technical elements
- Glassmorphism effects with backdrop-blur
- Custom scrollbar styling
```

### Animation Prompt

```
Implement Framer Motion animations:
- Scroll-triggered fade-ins with useInView hook
- Staggered children animations (0.1s delay)
- Hover effects (lift + scale) on interactive elements
- Scroll-linked parallax effects on hero section
- Use GPU-optimized properties (opacity, transform)
```

### Component Architecture Prompt

```
Create reusable shared components:
- Button: multiple variants (primary, outline, secondary), sizes, theme-aware
- Badge: color variants, optional pulse animation
- Card: glassmorphism, hover effects, multiple styles
- AnimatedSection: wrapper for scroll animations
- All components must support light/dark themes via context
```

### Theming Prompt

```
Implement theme system:
- React Context for global theme state (light/dark)
- useTheme hook for accessing theme in components
- Theme toggle in navbar
- Tailwind classes dynamically applied based on theme
- Dark: #0a0a0a background, light: #d5d5d5 background
```

### Responsive Design Prompt

```
Mobile-first responsive design:
- Hero text: 80px desktop → 44px mobile
- Layouts: multi-column desktop → single column mobile
- Grid systems: grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3
- Padding: py-16 md:py-24 lg:py-32
- Hidden elements: hidden md:block for desktop-only content
```

